hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider the power series in the variable $x$ given by
$$ \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} a_n x^n $$
where the sequence of coefficients $(a_n)_{n \geq 0}$ is defined as follows:
$$
a_n = \begin{cases}
    3^{n/2}  \text{if } n \text{ is even} \\
    2  \text{if } n \text{ is odd}
\end{cases}
$$
Determine the radius of convergence of this power series. Express your answer as a closed-form analytic expression.
